<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="52" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1554,1941]" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1554,1580]" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
1) body orange, except the head, hind leg, and posterior part of metasoma black; 2) fore wing hyaline yellowish, with two black bands; 3) head, in dorsal view, with gena slightly convex behind eyes; 4) face smooth and without a carina; 5) occipital carina slightly curved and reduced dorsally; 6) pronotum with the pocket-like structure not reduced longitudinally; 7) epicnemial carina absent; 8) sternite I with a low, rounded swelling posteriorly; 9) female with tarsal claw with square lobe, and with apex overtaking the lobe (tarsal claw single in males); 10) female with ovipositor sheath 0.75–0.9 × as long as the hind tibia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="52" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1554,1941]" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1770,1796]" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[361,432,1771,1797]" name="Brazil" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[444,614,1771,1797]" name="French Guiana" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">French Guiana</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[675,730,1771,1797]" name="Peru" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">Peru</collectingCountry>
. This is the first record of the species and genus for 
<collectingCountry box="[1325,1436,1771,1797]" name="Argentina" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">Argentina</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[159,250,1807,1833]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[166,1420,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-16@9.[166,1421,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 7. Geographical distribution of the Hymenoepimecis species. (A) H. atlantica sp. n.; (B) H. castilloi Pádua &amp; Sääksjärvi, 2020; (C) Hymenoepimecis japi Sobczak, Loffredo, Penteado-Dias &amp; Gonzaga, 2009; (D) H. ribeiroi Pádua &amp; Sobczak, 2015; (E) H. uberensis Pádua &amp; Onody, 2015; (F) H. veranii Loffredo &amp; Penteado-Dias, 2009." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911289" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911289/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">Fig. 7D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
